msgid "Updating Debian and Whonix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:6
#: 578dff1423044645b979b7c746e49ed0
msgid ""
"Despite Qubes shipping with :doc:`Debian Templates "
"</user/templates/debian/debian>`, most of Qubes core components run on "
"Fedora and thus our documentation has better coverage for Fedora. "
"However, Qubes has been working closely with the `Whonix "
"<https://whonix.org>`__ project which is based on Debian."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:8
#: c994157576384bad997fc0a25e65a6f1
msgid ""
"This troubleshooting guide is collection of tips about updating Whonix "
"that also pertain to updating the normal Debian package manager. If you "
"plan to use Debian heavily, **we highly recommend you install the Whonix "
"templates and use them to update your normal Debian template.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:10
#: d8c41172de4c4e30a6d639c4c8234228
msgid ""
"**Note: some of the links on this page go to documentation on Whonix’s "
"website**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:13
#: e983ff12cdad43ce890c31e822b7a3be
msgid "Updating Error Messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:16
#: 77821aaa5f464abba0e3e4931eba9b0b
msgid ""
"After running the commands to update Debian or Whonix, hopefully "
"everything will complete perfectly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:24
#: 228a7b225d794d039533d856e63be9dc
msgid ""
"However, if you see something like the following, then something went "
"wrong."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:51
#: 060a0c948ece4186ae29b67f0873f031
msgid ""
"This could be a temporary Tor exit relay or server failure that should "
"fix itself. Here are some simple things to try:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:53
#: ab6304da1d684f9e9bc3f5c27cda765e
msgid "Check if your network connection is functional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:55
#: a05af09f8e6c42f387ce4b408c8e510f
msgid ""
"Try to `change your Tor circuit <https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Arm>`__, "
"then try again"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:57
#: 3adea8bbfd424193a5e8b91d82711636
msgid ""
"Running `whonixcheck <https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Whonixcheck>`__ might "
"also help diagnose the problem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:61
#: 8a8c5d0bdcb9475cb8ae623e0d0ac355
msgid "Sometimes if you see a message such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:69
#: dba5a7ad0d944f7885ecca53cac27227
msgid "It helps to run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:77
#: 4d9309f9cf82435596f8dc8bdbc7808d
msgid "And then trying running the ``update`` and ``upgrade`` commands again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:85
#: 1764d4dbfc2846f7acf4d7fb91950a84
msgid ""
"*Please note: if you* `disabled the Whonix APT Repository "
"<https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Whonix-APT-"
"Repository#Disable_Whonix_APT_Repository>`__ *you’ll have to manually "
"check for new Whonix releases and* `manually install them from source "
"code <https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Dev/Build_Documentation>`__ *.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:88
#: 80548ef82ac745fa860fcd92a040157c
msgid "Never Install Unsigned Packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:91
#: b1f7628bf35d4fef8d9b4fc47be274a6
msgid "If you see something like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:101
#: 463ad9abbc8d4ca1bbb59ae0eaba74b2
msgid ""
"Don’t proceed! Press ``N`` and ``<enter>``. Running ``apt-get update`` "
"again should fix it. If not, something is broken or it’s a `Man in the "
"middle attack <https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Warning#Man-in-the-"
"middle_attacks>`__, which isn’t that unlikely, since we are updating over"
" Tor exit relays and some of them are malicious. Try to `change your Tor "
"circuit <https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Arm#Arm>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:104
#: 1a5f10ec8e8b416c984565da3f7442ed
msgid "Signature Verification Warnings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:107
#: 2406ba245d6b481a98bf6f5c3b409154
msgid ""
"There should be none at the moment. If there was such a warning, it would"
" look like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:115
#: 914e8fc1d44740e0856e44d9d5afe24a
msgid ""
"Even though, ``apt-get`` will automatically ignore repositories with "
"expired keys or signatures, you will not receive upgrades from that "
"repository. Unless the issue is already known/documented, it should be "
"reported so it can be further investigated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:117
#: 84d445bbbad5495996335e2d48781b4e
msgid ""
"There are two possible reasons why this could happen, either there is an "
"issue with the repository that the maintainers have to fix, or you are "
"victim of a `Man-in-the-middle_attacks "
"<https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Warning#Man-in-the-middle_attacks>`__. The "
"latter would not be a big issue and might go away after a while "
"automatically or try to `change your Tor circuit "
"<https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Arm#Arm>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:119
#: d3ec3b34d9b74ec48d92e553be0ea219
msgid ""
"In past various apt repositories were signed with expired key: `The Tor "
"Project’s apt repository key was expired "
"<https://trac.torproject.org/projects/tor/ticket/12994>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:121
#: 52b13e0864d84b7fa50689d13e61e442
msgid "You saw the following warning:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:132
#: 39fc5852be6b47ee866f70c93d68a706
msgid ""
"It had already been `reported "
"<https://trac.torproject.org/projects/tor/ticket/12994>`__. There was no "
"immediate danger. You could have just ignored it. Just make sure, you "
"never install unsigned packages as explained above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:134
#: 40b37638fd7a479880073bb82b4aa526
msgid ""
"If you were to see other signature verification errors, those should be "
"reported, but it shouldn’t happen at this time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:137
#: 963bfa91dd1b4ff896d835f7ec38fcb3
msgid "Changed Configuration Files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:140
#: ca7f3f7c703542f2bb7cb5435140bef1
msgid "If you see something like the following."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:158
#: 6e0594af7ca148169a81bcea2d7e56ea
msgid ""
"Be careful. If the updated file isn’t coming from Whonix specific package"
" (some are called ``whonix-...``), then press ``n``. Otherwise "
"anonymity/privacy/security settings deployed with Whonix might get lost. "
"If you are an advanced user and know better, you can of course manually "
"check the difference and merge them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:160
#: 1810884130ae4c11b23c1b0e2e57740b
msgid ""
"How could you find out if the file is coming from a Whonix specific "
"package or not?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:162
#: 347567150e944eb59dc73cfe826a67cd
msgid ""
"Whonix specific packages are sometimes called ``whonix-...``. In the "
"example above it’s saying ``Setting up ifupdown ...``, so the file isn’t "
"coming from a Whonix specific package. In this case, you should press "
"``n`` as advised in the paragraph above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/debian-and-whonix-update-troubleshooting.rst:164
#: d2a04ec0a11948ac8ab186b0dac81603
msgid ""
"If the package name does include ``whonix-...``, it’s a Whonix specific "
"package. In that case, your safest bet should be pressing ``y``, but then"
" you would lose your customized settings. You can re-add them afterwards."
" Such conflicts will hopefully rarely happen, if you use `Whonix modular "
"flexible .d style configuration folders "
"<https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Whonix_Configuration_Files>`__."
msgstr ""

